      <h1 class='title'>Chronically Sick and Disabled Persons Act</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 21 July 2004 vol 424 c51WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_51ws' title='Col. 51WS &mdash; HC Deb 21 July 2004 vol 424 c51WS' name='column_51ws' href='#column_51ws' rel='bookmark'>51WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040721_CWS_34'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/dr-stephen-ladyman' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040721_CWS_34' title='Link to this speech by Dr Stephen Ladyman' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/dr-stephen-ladyman" title="Dr Stephen Ladyman">The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Health (Dr. Stephen Ladyman)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The annual report for 2003 is being published today and copies have been placed in the Library. The report covers research and development work carried out by or on behalf of any Government Department in relation to equipment that might increase the range of activities and independence or well being of disabled people.</p><p>The current report places such research in the context of the national health service improvement plan, and outlines the role of assistive technology in making independent living easier for older people and people with disabilities. The report describes the wide range of Government funded projects supporting the development, introduction and evaluation of assistive technology.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
